&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Analyst III&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;itD is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Business Analyst III&lt;/strong&gt; to drive demand forecasting and business planning for Reality Labs&#39; VR headset and wearables portfolio. The ideal candidate will bring deep experience in demand forecasting, business analytics, and sales planning, with a proven track record of delivering accurate forecasts and actionable business insights that influence production, launch, and go-to-market decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Remote (U.S.) – PST preferred, with strong preference for candidates able to work &lt;strong&gt;3 days onsite in Burlingame, CA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration: &lt;/strong&gt;12 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Rate:&lt;/strong&gt; $30 - $32 per hour, depending on experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;We provide comprehensive medical benefits, a 401(k) plan, paid holidays, and more.&lt;br&gt;Please note that we are only considering direct W2 candidates at this time, as we are unable to offer sponsorship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain bottom-up sell-through and sell-in demand forecasts for VR headsets and wearable hardware products using quantitative and qualitative data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with sales account managers, category managers, marketing teams, channel operations, and data analysts to improve forecast accuracy and identify business growth opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze weekly, monthly, quarterly, and annual sales performance, identifying trends, risks, and opportunities across hardware and accessory product lines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own actual-versus-forecast performance analysis by identifying root causes, recommending corrective actions, and monitoring forecast effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present forecast assumptions, business insights, and performance updates to Reality Labs leadership and cross-functional stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop forecasting models by analyzing large datasets, identifying trends, dependencies, and correlations to improve planning accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support production planning and product launch decisions through close collaboration with channel operations and business teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create high-quality reports, dashboards, and executive presentations while managing ad hoc forecasting requests and business analyses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend regular internal practice community meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with your itD practice team on industry thought leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete client case studies and learning material (blogs, media material).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build out material to contribute to the Digital Transformation practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend internal itD networking events (in person and virtual).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with leadership on career fast-track opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications and Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in hardware product demand forecasting, planning, or forecasting analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in business strategy, business analytics, finance, sales planning, or related analytical roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building demand forecasting models for consumer hardware products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency with Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets, Google Workspace, and PowerPoint.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience performing quantitative analysis and translating data into business recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong cross-functional collaboration and stakeholder presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
