&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Analyst IV (Product Lifecycle Management Analyst)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;itD is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Data Analyst IV (Product Lifecycle Management Analyst)&lt;/strong&gt; to support product lifecycle operations for cutting-edge AR/VR technologies within Reality Labs. This role will play a critical part in managing product data, engineering changes, part creation, and product configurations throughout the product lifecycle—from concept and prototype through production and end-of-life. The ideal candidate will bring deep experience in Product Lifecycle Management (PLM), engineering change management, and product data governance, along with a proven track record of supporting complex hardware product development in fast-paced, high-tech environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Onsite – Sunnyvale, CA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration:&lt;/strong&gt; 12 Months (Potential for Extension and/or Conversion)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide comprehensive medical benefits, a 401k plan, paid holidays, and more. Please note that we are only considering direct W2 candidates at this time, as we are unable to offer sponsorship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain manufacturer, vendor, and business part numbers within the PLM system while ensuring data accuracy, completeness, and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage product data throughout the product lifecycle, including concept, prototype, new product introduction (NPI), and sustaining activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and release complex Bills of Materials (BOMs) for electronic, mechanical, and system-level products based on engineering and manufacturing requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiate, track, and manage Engineering Change Orders (ECOs), deviations, stop ships, and non-revision changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Engineering, Program Management, Supply Chain, Manufacturing, and Logistics teams to support product configuration and material planning requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support prototype builds, asset tracking, and product documentation efforts by maintaining accurate part and configuration data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide end-user support, troubleshoot PLM-related issues, and advise stakeholders on best practices for product documentation and change management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend regular internal practice community meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with your itD practice team on industry thought leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete client case studies and learning material (blogs, media material).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build out material to contribute to the Digital Transformation practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend internal itD networking events (in person and virtual).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with leadership on career fast-track opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications and Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in a high-tech, fast-paced environment utilizing Product Lifecycle Management (PLM) systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with Part Creation and Product Data Management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience managing Engineering Change Orders (ECOs), deviations, and change control processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating and maintaining Approved Manufacturer Lists (AMLs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating and releasing complex Bills of Materials (BOMs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working cross-functionally with Engineering, Supply Chain, Manufacturing, and Program Management teams.&lt;/li&gt;
